news.title: Omaxe raises Rs 440 crore from Varde Partners to expedite construction, expand business
news.para: The company will deploy the funds for expediting construction and delivery of its projects as well as for expansion, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Probe illegal sand activity in Goa: HC to chief secretary, DGP
news.para: The court also directed the in-charge of Pernem police station and mamlatdar to file a detailed affidavit about the incidents.

news.title: Offline submission for big projects in Nashik
news.para: The decision to this effect was taken due to technical glitches in software and there had been demand from builders and architects to allow offline submission of building plans for at least the large projects.

news.title: Adani lines up financing, frontrunner for Holcim India's assets worth $10 billion
news.para: Switzerland-based Holcim that globally merged with French rival Lafarge in 2015 to create a mega entity LafargeHolcim – a European cement and buildings material giant -- was forced to go through several restructurings to comply with anti-trust regulators around the world, by divesting assets across Europe and Asia, including India.

news.title: Panchayat order a wake-up call for builders in Kochi
news.para: It was last week that the Chengamanad panchayat in Aluva issued a notice to an owner of a flat in ‘Anvita Residency’, an eleven-storey building at Desham Junction, to demolish all the constructions attached to their flats, citing that the modification works would affect the safety of the entire building.

news.title: Over 9,000 beneficiaries to get pattas: Andhra Pradesh health minister
news.para: After inspecting the arrangements for Jagan’s visit to Pydiwada in Sabbavaram mandal on the outskirts of Port City along with former minister M Srinivasa Rao on Monday, Rajni said more than 9,000 beneficiaries would get house sites pattas on 313 acres of land.

news.title: Nagpur civic body collects only 44% of Rs 257 crore current property tax
news.para: According to data obtained from NMC’s property tax department, of the Rs256.87 crore tax calculated for 7.56 lakh properties, the NMC could collect only Rs111.4 crore.

news.title: UT adviser okays sale of Chandigarh housing board properties on freehold
news.para: In connection with residential properties, directions were issued to the CHB to deposit required conversion charges from leasehold to freehold to the housing department, and start e-auction of the properties.

news.title: Housing prices may rise 8% this fiscal: Report
news.para: ​"The current housing sales uptick and increased demand is end user driven and not speculative. Hence, the hike in prices will be sustainable and is likely to be incremental. Prices were up 6 per cent pan-India in FY22," the rating agency said in a statement.

news.title: Gurugram: Valuation agency, engineer finalised for Chintels Paradiso audit
news.para: A DTCP official said the department will also hand over remaining documents to the IIT-D team which is carrying out a structural audit of the society. Residents of the highrise had earlier alleged that the audit was getting delayed owing to non-submission of a few mandatory documents to the IIT-D team.

news.title: Builders hike prices by 10% in NCR, may have to increase prices again over rising raw material cost
news.para: The developers had been absorbing the cost impact until now, but with raw material costs continuing to climb, that won't be possible as margins have plummeted, leaving no room for further adjustment.

news.title: Indian realty attracts $943 million investments in Q1; office space leads
news.para: The real estate sector has attracted investments worth $943 million during the quarter led by the office segment and a comeback of retail real estate, showed a JLL India report.

news.title: Banks release Rs 280 crore for completion of stalled Amrapali projects, Dhoni moves SC
news.para: A bench of Justices UU Lalit and Bela M Trivedi took note of the submission of advocate Alok Kumar, appearing for the consortium of banks, that Rs 280 crore will be released to ASPIRE, from where it will be used for funding of the incomplete projects.

news.title: Century Textiles back in black with Rs 84 crore net income in Q4
news.para: He also sounded upbeat about realty business following the launch of Birla Niyaara at Worli in central Mumbai, where it has already received Rs 1,200 crore of bookings so far.

news.title: Mushrooming of illegal colonies across country is menace to urban development: SC
news.para: "Mushrooming of illegal colonies in all these cities in this country, the consequences are so drastic. We have seen floods in Hyderabad and Kerala, all this is because of irregular colonies.
